snippet.title: The Devil Wears Prada 2 | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Everybody wants this. 

Meryl Streep, Anne Hathaway, Emily Blunt, and Stanley Tucci return in The Devil Wears Prada 2, in theaters May 1. Watch the full trailer now. 

Almost 20 years after making their iconic turn as Miranda, Andy, Emily and Nigel—Meryl Streep, Anne Hathaway, Emily Blunt and Stanley Tucci return to the fashionable streets of New York City and the sleek offices of Runway Magazine in the eagerly awaited sequel to the 2006 phenomenon that defined a generation. 
 
The film reunites the original main cast with director David Frankel and writer Aline Brosh McKenna, and introduces an all-new runway of characters including Kenneth Branagh, Simone Ashley, Justin Theroux, Lucy Liu, Patrick Brammall, Caleb Hearon, Helen J. Shen, Pauline Chalamet, B.J. Novak and Conrad Ricamora. Tracie Thoms and Tibor Feldman also reprise their roles as “Lily” and “Irv” from the first film. 
 
“The Devil Wears Prada 2” is produced by Wendy Finerman, and executive produced by Michael Bederman, Karen Rosenfelt and Aline Brosh McKenna. The film debuts exclusively in theaters May 1.

snippet.title: Ruwa Jin - Jin Jin
snippet.description:
Ruwa Jin - “Jin Jin”

✦ Available on all streaming platforms:
🟢 Spotify:
⚪️ Apple Music:

Follow Ruwa Jin:
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/ruwajin

“Jin Jin” speaks of a quiet, spiritual kind of love.
A presence that protects without control,
a soul that stays close when words fall silent.

The song reflects on being someone’s inner shelter -
not loud, not forceful, but constant.
Gentle Afrobeat rhythms meet soulful emotion,
creating a warm, spiritual calm between love and faith.

✦ Genre: afro-soul · spiritual afrobeat · emotional pop · ambient soul
✦ Mood: protective · warm · melancholic · spiritual · love
✦ Sound: soft percussion · gentle pads · emotional vocals · airy mix


📝 LYRICS:

[Intro]
Mm…
Yeah

[Verse 1]
You said love is like a flame
But we burn slow, never the same
You been searchin’ for a sign
But I’ve been right here, all the time

When you cry, I feel it too
Every breath, I walk with you
You don’t see, but deep inside
I’m the light you try to hide

[Chorus]
I’m your Jin Jin
Your peace when the rain falls in
I’m your Jin Jin
Your calm when the storm begins
I’m your Jin Jin
Your truth when your faith feels thin
I’m your Jin Jin
Forever within

[Verse 2]
I know your heart been bruised before
You closed the lock, then lost the door
But love don’t fade, it just transforms
From pain to light, from loss to warmth

I see the prayers you never said
The dreams still lying in your bed
You don’t need to face it all alone
You can rest, I’ll guide you home

[Chorus]
I’m your Jin Jin
Your peace when the rain falls in
I’m your Jin Jin
Your calm when the storm begins
I’m your Jin Jin
Your truth when your faith feels thin
I’m your Jin Jin
Forever within

[Bridge]
Even when the silence breaks
Even when the soul still aches
I’ll be there through every phase
Your light inside my waves

[Outro]
Mmm…
You don’t have to fight again
I’m your Jin Jin
Till the end

snippet.title: SAME SUN (OFFICAL MOVIE TRAILER)
snippet.description:
The film SAME SUN (http://same-sun-film.com/) tells the story of Wiebke Lühmann's journey from Freiburg to the Cape of Good Hope. Honest, raw, and close to the inner and outer challenges of a 430-day bicycle trip. Her journey takes her through 22 countries, Sahara storms, the rain season, the Congo Basin, and the deserts of Namibia. 

At the heart of it all is her desire for independence, which Wiebke pursues as a twin sister, a 30-year-old woman, and a traveler on a continent where she still has much to learn. A 90-minute adventure film that is not about performance and records, but about encounters. 

Trailer: El Flamingo & Fabienne Engel
Camera: Fabienne Engel & Wiebke Lühmann
Supporter: Wilier Triestina, Ortlieb Waterproof, Ryzon Apparel, Supernova Design, Canon, Schwalbe
